Source.Name: composable-kernel
Source.Summary: Performance Portable Programming Model for Machine Learning Tensor Operators
Source.Description: The Composable Kernel (CK) library provides a programming model for writing performance-critical kernels for machine learning workloads across multiple architectures (GPUs, CPUs, etc.). The CK library uses general purpose kernel languages, such as HIP C++.
